The evidence with the title 'Soft money political spending by nonprofits tripled in 2008 ' says Feb 25, 2009  ... Fueled by unlimited “ soft money ” donations , section 501(c)nonprofit groups and section 527 political organizations spent morethan $ 400 million in the 2008 federal elections . This figure is largelybased on CFI's analysis of Federal Election Commission ( FEC ) AndInternal Revenue Service ( IRS)reports.
